To troubleshoot slow Wi-Fi- 
Start with unplugging modem and router for a minute and then plug them back in to refresh the connection. 
check for devices connected to the wifi, if there is too much devices connected then try removing unused or less frequesntly used ones.
Most of the time, internet speed slows down due to obstruction or obstacles. Place your router in a cemtralized positions. 
Check for and install any available firmware updates for the router, as these can improve performance and security. 
Check your computers network drivers, if they are outdated then update them.
